The same bill that extended tax cuts and cut social programs also contained the mining provision for Twin Metals, granting it durable rights near a protected wilderness and barring most judicial review. The Organization for Economic Cooperation and Development reported that Trump\'92s tariffs were slowing U.S. growth, while the Congressional Budget Office found that the omnibus bill would add trillions to the deficit and cause sixteen million people to lose health insurance. Yet the White House press office claimed the bill would bring the largest deficit reduction in decades. Economic data itself became contested terrain, with staffing shortages at the Bureau of Labor Statistics forcing greater reliance on rough estimates and economists questioning the accuracy of inflation reports. In such a setting, those with access to private information and influence over narrative\'97donors, lobbyists, and the executive\'97could shape perceptions of prosperity and pain to suit their aims. Inequality was not a flaw; it was the design.\
